I still don't see why you keep saying we women are slaves to our husbands. My dh and I would be what you refer to as &quot;fundies&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We take the Bible as the literal Word of God. We are also what you would call &quot;born-again&quot; (never liked those two terms ... always said such sarcasm). We have made decisions in our lives which allow me to stay home the majority of the time with our son. Therefore, most of my &quot;work&quot; is in the house - but then, I don't mind doing any of it. I'm not slaving - I'm home, he's not, it has to get done. I'm not going to say, &quot;You do all the housework when you get home because I'm not your slave.&quot; As well, I cook 90% of the time, typically because I enjoy cooking and don't enjoy eating most of what dh cooks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (unless he bbq's). He, though, does all the dishes. When he gets home from work, he takes the baby (I guess he's technically a toddler), and lets me have some free time. When it comes to decisions, more often than not, he defers to me because he usually likes my suggestions more than his own. But, if there is a time where we can't agree on something, I defer to him. Why get in an argument over it? Someone has to give sometimes; I make an effort to give. (And to be honest, there are many more times when he makes the effort to give in to me instead.) Point being, we are not a &quot;master-slave&quot; couple. We are equals in our relationship. But, there will come a time where someone has to have the final say in something ... I choose to let him have it (though not all the time, I can be pretty stubborn!). <br>
<br>
Again, not expecting you to agree with me or accept what I'm saying. But, I ask that you try to respect our decisions and choices. <br>
